.TH scrollok 3
.SH NAME
\*Lscrollok\*O \- Enables screen scrolling
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.sS
\*L#include <curses.h>\*O

\*Lint scrollok(\*Vwin\*L, \*Vbf\*L)
    WINDOW \(**\*Vwin\*L;
    bool \*Vbf\*L;\*O
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "scrollok subroutine"
This option controls what happens when the cursor is moved off
the edge of the specified window or scrolling region,
either from a newline on the bottom line, or when the last
character of the last line is typed.  If disabled (\*Lbf\*O is FALSE),
the cursor is left on the bottom line.
If enabled, the window is scrolled up one line and then refreshed.
.SH RETURN VALUES
.PP
The \*Lscrollok\*O function returns OK on success and ERR on error.
.EQ
